Business Brief -- Promus Cos.:
   Harrah's Unit to Operate
   Riverboat Casino in Illinois
The project is subject to approval of state gambling
regulators and other authorities.
   Plans call for a 210-foot boat that will accommodate 1,000
passengers. The three-level floating casino is expected to
include about 500 slots and other machine games and about 30
table games such as craps, blackjack and roulette.
   Promus is one of several public and private companies
looking for profits in the newly legalized riverboat casinos.
Hilton Hotels Corp., Beverly Hills, Calif., plans to launch a
boat in New Orleans, and several boats already ply the waters
of Iowa.